@Node "Bugs" "PrintManager.guide/Bugs"

@{b}Possible problems and their solution
************************************@{ub}

 If you discover any bugs, please send a detailed bug-report to the @{"Author" Link "Author"}.
Don't forget to add a descprition of your configuration!
  
 ° Since I don't own a serial printer, I wasn't able to verify if PrintManager
   correctly works with such a kind of printer.
 
 ° If PrintManager doesn't recognize some programs sending data to the printer,
   you should activate the DEVICE option.
   
 ° While PrintManager is printing a file via the datatypes-system, the Workbench
   Screen can't be closed. This is because PrintManager opens an invisible window
   on the screen.
   
 ° If the program seems to "hang" when trying to print a file via the datatypes-
   system, you should activate the DEVICE option.
 
 ° In the case that you use TurboPrint by IrseeSoft, you must deactivate the
   TurboPAR option of TP. Otherwise PrtMan cannot recognize any job.
 
 ° pit.device: The PDCMD_QUERY of this device is broken this means that PM
   cannot determine the printer state.

 ° PowerCache may cause block errors when PrintManager saves temporary data on
   a cached disk. Seems that PC has some problems when reading and writing a
   file at the same time. This is not a bug of PM!

 ° Problems with the HyperCOM io-boards have been reported, either the hardware
   or software of these boards seem to be buggy (bad printerstate is returned). 
   CHECKPRINTERSTATE=NO might help to workaround the problem.

@EndNode
